{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"62d3cf46-78e3-4736-9bff-dffff977f98c","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is forwarded to the test platform. You'll need these packages referenced in your test project:\n\n| Old (VSTest) | New package needed |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\nAlso ensure your test project sets `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` and `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` (for MSTest) or the equivalent for your framework.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1f19ab14-31e9-48a3-bd4d-ca76851a77d4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. They want to know what the equivalent command would look like.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The key differences are:\n\n1. `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n2. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n4. `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n5. `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n6. `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, you can still use `dotnet test` but the arguments change, or you can run the test executable directly. The exact syntax depends on whether you're using `dotnet test` or running the platform executable.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform enabled, most arguments like `--filter`, `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and `--crashdump` work similarly, though some are forwarded differently to the platform than they were with the older test runner. the `--filter` argument with `dotnet test`, though some of the diagnostic options like `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` need to be passed after `--` to reach the test platform directly. I could also run the test executable directly and pass all arguments to it without worrying about the `dotnet test` wrapper's argument parsing.\n\nThe key packages needed are the Microsoft.Testing.Extensions for trx reporting, code coverage, and the crash/hang dump diagnostics, though the hang dump option appears to be cut off in the list.","outputTokens":1389,"requestId":"E3CB:2C00FF:1D37497:202CC62:6A05204A"},"id":"6b64183f-d01d-49e6-a3e6-3cf53e89a296","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:07:46.752Z","parentId":"65f0d4b6-730d-47b4-8b02-3b0946593a9d"}
